ge of solutions to a problem that is rooted in our nation’s slave history and that is worsened by ongoing conflict over immigration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aAgricultural laborersxLabor unionszFloridazImmokalee. 0aAgricultural laborerszFloridazImmokalee. 0aFood industry and tradezFloridazImmokaleexEmployees. 4aFood Studies. 4aHistory. 4aLabor History.  aFlorida farmworkers, labor activism, agriculture, agricultural labor, labor history, Coalition of Immokalee Workers, worker-driven social responsibility initiative.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066587140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171431340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501714313423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501714313/original  a978-3-11-066587-1  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles